      "role": "tool",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "content: '# Web Document\n\n\n  ## Metadata\n\n\n  - title: Get an Appointment\n\n  - url: https://sa.dmv.ca.gov/DMV/ukp.aspx?pid=1&ruleid=341\n\n  - source: California Department of Motor Vehicles\n\n  - domain: sa.dmv.ca.gov\n\n\n  ## Content\n\n\n  # Get an appointment\n\n\n  Apply, renew, replace! Appointments available.\n\n\n  Available appointment service choices shown on the DMV appointment page include:\n\n\n  - REAL ID Driver''s License / REAL ID\n\n  - Driver''s License / ID Card Renewal\n\n  - Vehicle / Vessel Registration\n\n\n  The appointment page directs customers to choose the DMV service that matches the\n  transaction they need before continuing. The service choice is the starting point\n  for scheduling because different DMV transactions use different application steps\n  and office requirements.\n\n\n  Customers who need a driver-license or identification-card transaction should identify\n  whether they are applying, renewing, replacing, or updating a card before choosing\n  the next step. Some services can start online and may still require an office visit\n  to finish. Other services are handled online, at a kiosk, with a DMV business partner,\n  or by mail.\n\n\n  For driver-license customers, the DMV appointment and application pages direct customers\n  to complete the relevant online application or service request before visiting a\n  DMV office when an in-person visit is required. Customers should select the service\n  category that matches the driver-license transaction they need to complete.\n\n\n  '\nmetadata: {}\ntitle: Get an Appointment\nurl: https://sa.dmv.ca.gov/DMV/ukp.aspx?pid=1&ruleid=341"
        }
      ],
      "tool_call_id": "call_93yXn0jE6X181mOB2p1HJbd9",
      "tool_call": {
