    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": "Yes. The right California DMV appointment option depends on what you need to do:\n\n- **First California driver’s license** → *Driver’s License / ID Card* or *Original Driver’s License*\n- **Renew an existing license** → *Driver’s License / ID Card Renewal*\n- **Lost, stolen, or damaged license** → *Driver’s License / ID Card Replacement*\n- **Change your name or address** → *Driver’s License / ID Card* update service; some changes can be done online\n- **REAL ID** → *REAL ID Driver’s License / REAL ID*\n- **Written/knowledge test** → usually an *Original Driver’s License* appointment\n- **Behind-the-wheel test** → *Behind-the-Wheel Drive Test*\n- **Senior/in-person issue or another special matter** → choose the closest driver-license service, or contact the DMV if no option fits\n\nThe DMV’s official appointment page is: [Get an Appointment](https://sa.dmv.ca.gov/DMV/ukp.aspx?pid=1&ruleid=341).\n\nWhat exactly are you trying to do—get your first license, renew, replace, get a REAL ID, take a test, or something else?"
        }
      ],
      "tool_calls": null
    }
